comments.body:
@PowerShell/wg-powershell-engine 
This was done to follow the ANSI documentation (https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/console/console-virtual-terminal-sequences) rather than perpetuate the older console color enum.

<blockquote><img src="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/media/logos/logo-ms-social.png" width="48" align="right"><div><strong><a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/console/console-virtual-terminal-sequences">Console Virtual Terminal Sequences - Windows Console</a></strong></div><div>Virtual terminal sequences are control character sequences that can control cursor movement, color/font mode, and other operations when written to the output stream.</div></blockquote>
